# Cyber Safety Awareness for Students

As digital technology becomes part of everyday learning, students are increasingly exposed to online risks. This document highlights practical ways to stay safe online — focusing on email safety, password hygiene, and safe browsing habits.

# 2. Email Safety
- Avoid opening emails from unknown senders.
- Never click suspicious links or download unexpected attachments.
- Verify the sender’s email address carefully.
- Report phishing attempts to a teacher or system administrator.

# 3. Password Hygiene
- Use strong passwords that include letters, numbers, and special symbols.
- Avoid using the same password for multiple accounts.
- Change your passwords regularly.
- Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) wherever possible.

# 4. Safe Browsing
- Always check for "https://" in website addresses.
- Avoid sharing personal details on untrusted websites.
- Install antivirus software and keep it updated.
- Be cautious of pop-up ads and free downloads.
